  // ── SAFETY: 80 ──
  add(1,"Home","Overloading electrical outlets increases risk of:",["Electrical fires and short circuits","Better power supply","Faster charging","Improved connectivity"],0,"Use one plug per outlet or a surge protector. Never daisy-chain extension cords.","Don't overload outlets. Use surge protectors. Check wire ratings.");
  add(1,"Home","Cleaning chemicals should be stored:",["In a locked cabinet out of children's reach","Under the kitchen sink openly","On the dining table","In the bedroom"],0,"Many household chemicals are poisonous. Store high, locked, and separate from food.","Lock cleaning chemicals away from children. Never mix bleach with ammonia.");
  add(1,"Home","LPG gas leaks smell like:",["Nothing — LPG is naturally odorless, but mercaptan is added for a rotten-egg smell","Fresh flowers","Burning plastic","Wet soil"],0,"If you smell gas: don't touch switches, open windows, turn off cylinder, exit.","Gas smell? NO switches. Open windows. Turn off cylinder. Exit immediately.");
  add(1,"Home","Carbon monoxide is dangerous because it is:",["Colorless and odorless — poisoning happens without any warning","Bright green and easy to see","Very loud when leaking","Only dangerous outdoors"],0,"Install CO detectors near bedrooms. Symptoms: headache, dizziness, nausea.","Install carbon monoxide detectors. CO is invisible, odorless, and deadly.");
  add(1,"Home","The best way to extinguish a small grease fire in a pan:",["Cover with a metal lid to cut off oxygen","Pour water on it","Fan it with a towel","Throw flour on it"],0,"Cutting oxygen supply smothers the fire. Never use water — it causes explosive splatter.","Pan fire: cover with lid. NEVER water. Turn off heat source.");
  add(1,"Home","Children should learn to call emergency services by age:",["4-5 years — they should know 112","Only teenagers","Only adults need to know","Age 15"],0,"Teach children: what is 112, when to call, their home address, and their parents' names.","Teach kids 112, home address, and parents' phone number by age 5.");
  add(1,"Home","Medicines should be stored:",["Near the kitchen stove for easy access","In a cool dry place away from sunlight and children's reach","In the bathroom near the shower","On the dining table"],0,"Heat moisture and sunlight degrade medications. Use a high cabinet with child lock.","Medicines: cool + dry + out of reach. Check expiry dates monthly.");
  add(1,"Home","A fire extinguisher at home should be:",["Easily accessible near the kitchen and exit routes","Hidden in a closet","Under the bed","In the attic"],0,"Everyone in the house should know the PASS technique: Pull Aim Squeeze Sweep.","Keep extinguisher near kitchen. Know PASS: Pull Aim Squeeze Sweep.");
  add(1,"Home","Loose rugs on smooth floors are dangerous because:",["They look untidy","They cause slips and falls especially for elderly people","They collect too much dust","They damage the floor"],0,"Use non-slip pads under rugs. Falls are the leading cause of injury for seniors.","Secure loose rugs with non-slip pads. Prevent falls especially for elderly.");
  add(1,"Home","Sharp objects like knives should be stored:",["In a drawer with a knife block or magnetic strip away from children","Loose in a cluttered drawer","On the kitchen counter edge","In a bag"],0,"Proper knife storage prevents cuts and keeps blades sharper longer.","Knife block or magnetic strip. Never loose in drawers where hands search blindly.");

  add(1,"Road","Seat belt use in rear seats is:",["Mandatory by law in India and reduces fatality risk by 25-75%","Optional always","Only required on highways","Only for children"],0,"Rear passengers without belts become projectiles in crashes injuring front occupants too.","Rear seat belts: mandatory and lifesaving. Unbelted rear passengers endanger everyone.");
  add(1,"Road","When an ambulance approaches from behind you should:",["Slow down and pull to the left side to let it pass","Speed up to get out of the way","Stop in the middle of the road","Ignore it and continue driving"],0,"Every minute of delay can cost a life. Pull left let them pass then resume.","Give way to ambulances. Pull left. Someone's life depends on those minutes.");
  add(1,"Road","Jaywalking means:",["Crossing the road at unauthorized or dangerous points","Crossing the road at designated crossings","Walking on the footpath","Jogging on the road"],0,"Use zebra crossings pedestrian signals and foot over-bridges. Jaywalking causes 60%+ pedestrian deaths.","Cross at zebra crossings only. Jaywalking causes most pedestrian fatalities.");
  add(1,"Road","Driving at night is more dangerous primarily because:",["Reduced visibility lower depth perception and higher chance of drowsy or impaired drivers","Roads are worse at night","Cars perform poorly at night","Traffic rules change"],0,"Fatal crashes are 3x more likely at night. Use headlights reduce speed stay alert.","Night driving: 3x more fatal crashes. Reduce speed. Stay fully alert.");
  add(1,"Road","Using high beam in city traffic is dangerous because:",["It blinds oncoming drivers causing momentary vision loss","It uses more fuel","It damages headlights","It is not bright enough"],0,"Switch to low beam when other vehicles approach. High beam is for empty dark roads only.","High beam: only on dark empty roads. Switch to low in traffic. Blinding others kills.");
  add(1,"Road","Zebra crossing gives pedestrians:",["Right of way — vehicles must stop when pedestrians are on the crossing","No special rights","Right of way only on Sundays","Priority only for elderly"],0,"Pedestrians on zebra crossings have legal right of way in India.","Zebra crossing = pedestrian priority. Drivers MUST stop.");
  add(1,"Road","Two-wheeler riders should wear:",["Open-face helmets for comfort","ISI-marked full-face helmets with chin strap fastened","Any hat or cap","Helmets only on highways"],0,"Full-face helmets protect the chin and jaw which are injured in 35% of motorcycle crashes.","Full-face ISI helmet with strap fastened. Chin injuries are 35% of bike crashes.");
  add(1,"Road","Speed breakers are installed to:",["Annoy drivers","Slow traffic in areas with high pedestrian activity schools and hospitals","Damage vehicles","Increase fuel consumption"],0,"Speed breakers save lives near schools hospitals and residential areas.","Slow down at speed breakers. They protect children and pedestrians.");
  add(1,"Road","The golden hour in accident response refers to:",["The first hour after a traumatic injury when medical treatment is most effective","Rush hour traffic","Sunset driving time","Peak accident time"],0,"Getting accident victims to a hospital within 60 minutes dramatically improves survival rates.","Golden hour: first 60 minutes after accident. Quick treatment saves lives. Call 112.");
  add(1,"Road","Lane discipline means:",["Driving in any lane you prefer","Staying in your lane using indicators before changing and not weaving","Only using the fast lane","Driving in the center of the road"],0,"Poor lane discipline is a major cause of accidents in India. Indicate before changing lanes.","Stay in lane. Indicate before changing. Don't weave. Lane discipline saves lives.");

  add(1,"Cyber","A strong password should be:",["At least 12 characters with uppercase lowercase numbers and symbols","Your name and birth year","Just numbers for simplicity","A common word"],0,"Use a unique password for each account. Consider a password manager.","12+ chars mixed case + numbers + symbols. Never reuse passwords.");
  add(1,"Cyber","If someone calls claiming your Aadhaar is misused and demands money:",["Hang up — this is a scam. No government body demands money over phone","Pay immediately to avoid problems","Share your Aadhaar number to verify","Transfer money to the account they provide"],0,"UIDAI never calls demanding money. Report such calls to cybercrime.gov.in.","Aadhaar scam calls: HANG UP. Report at cybercrime.gov.in. UIDAI never demands money.");
  add(1,"Cyber","Free public WiFi should not be used for:",["Browsing news websites","Banking transactions or entering passwords without a VPN","Checking weather","Reading articles"],0,"Hackers can intercept unencrypted data on public WiFi. Use mobile data for sensitive tasks.","Public WiFi: browse only. Use mobile data or VPN for banking and passwords.");
  add(1,"Cyber","SIM swapping fraud starts when scammers:",["Convince your mobile carrier to transfer your number to their SIM","Steal your physical SIM","Clone your phone","Hack your WiFi router"],0,"If your SIM suddenly stops working contact your carrier immediately — you may have minutes.","SIM stops working suddenly? Call carrier IMMEDIATELY. Possible SIM swap fraud.");
  add(1,"Cyber","The safest way to verify a suspicious link is to:",["Click it to see where it goes","Hover over it to preview the URL without clicking or type the website address manually","Forward it to friends for opinion","Copy paste it into your browser"],0,"Hovering reveals the actual URL destination. Phishing links look similar but lead to fake sites.","Don't click suspicious links. Hover to see the real URL. Type addresses manually.");
  add(1,"Cyber","Deepfake videos can be spotted by looking for:",["Unnatural blinking lip sync issues and odd lighting or skin texture","Perfect quality always means deepfake","Deepfakes are always obvious","Only AI can detect deepfakes"],0,"Look for inconsistencies around the face edges blinking patterns and lip sync accuracy.","Spotting deepfakes: check blinking lip sync skin texture and face edges.");
  add(1,"Cyber","Two-step verification SMS codes can be intercepted through:",["SIM swapping allowing attackers to receive your OTPs","They can never be intercepted","Only by the phone manufacturer","Only by the government"],0,"Use authenticator apps instead of SMS for 2FA. They generate codes offline.","SMS 2FA is vulnerable to SIM swap. Use Google Authenticator or Authy instead.");

  add(1,"Disaster","During a lightning storm you should avoid:",["Staying inside a building","Standing under tall trees or in open fields near metal objects","Crouching low in a ditch","Being in a car with windows closed"],0,"Lightning strikes the tallest point. Stay indoors or crouch low away from trees water and metal.","Lightning: stay indoors. If outside crouch low away from trees and water.");
  add(1,"Disaster","Earthquake preparedness includes:",["Only having an emergency kit","Securing heavy furniture to walls bolting water heater and having an escape plan","Nothing — earthquakes cannot be prepared for","Only stocking food"],0,"Secure bookshelves TVs and water heaters. Practice Drop Cover Hold On drills.","Bolt heavy furniture. Know exits. Practice Drop Cover Hold On.");
  add(1,"Disaster","During a landslide warning:",["Move away from slopes river valleys and unstable ground immediately","Stay near hillsides to watch","Climb to higher slopes","Stand under a bridge"],0,"Landslides move fast and are deadly. Move perpendicular to the slide path.","Landslide warning: move away from slopes immediately. Don't wait.");
  add(1,"Disaster","Heat wave safety includes:",["Staying hydrated staying indoors during peak heat and wearing light loose clothing","Exercising outdoors at noon","Drinking only cold beverages","Taking very cold showers constantly"],0,"Drink water even when not thirsty. Avoid sun between 11 AM and 4 PM.","Heat wave: water water water. Stay indoors 11AM-4PM. Light loose clothes.");
  add(1,"Disaster","After a flood you should only drink:",["Any available water","Boiled or purified water as regular sources may be contaminated","River water","Rainwater collected during the flood"],0,"Floods contaminate water with sewage chemicals and debris. Boil for 1 minute minimum.","Post-flood: BOIL all water for 1 minute minimum. Regular water is contaminated.");

  add(1,"Travel","When using ride-sharing apps at night:",["Verify the car model license plate and driver name before getting in and share trip details","Get into any car that stops","Only check the car color","Trust anyone wearing a uniform"],0,"Share your live trip with a trusted contact. Sit in the back seat.","Verify car details BEFORE entering. Share trip. Sit in back. Trust instincts.");
  add(1,"Travel","Travel insurance is important because:",["It covers medical emergencies trip cancellations lost baggage and evacuation","It is just a waste of money","It is legally required everywhere","It only covers flight delays"],0,"A medical emergency abroad without insurance can cost lakhs. Always get covered.","Travel insurance: covers medical emergencies abroad. One accident can bankrupt you.");
  add(1,"Travel","Before international travel always:",["Only pack clothes","Check visa requirements get travel insurance and share itinerary with trusted contacts","Avoid all preparation","Cancel your credit cards"],0,"Also keep copies of passport visa and insurance — both digital and physical.","Travel prep: visa + insurance + itinerary shared + document copies.");

  // ── MONEY: 80 ──
  add(2,"Saving","The 50-30-20 budget rule allocates income as:",["50% needs 30% wants 20% savings","50% savings 30% needs 20% wants","Equal thirds","80% spending 20% taxes"],0,"Needs: rent food utilities. Wants: dining entertainment. Savings: investments emergency fund.","Try 50-30-20: needs wants savings. Adjust based on your income.");
  add(2,"Saving","An emergency fund should cover:",["3-6 months of living expenses","1 month of expenses","Only medical costs","1 week of expenses"],0,"This buffer protects against job loss medical emergencies and unexpected costs.","Build 3-6 months expenses as emergency fund before investing.");
  add(2,"Saving","Paying yourself first means:",["Automatically saving a fixed amount before spending on anything else","Buying things before paying bills","Earning extra income","Paying bills early"],0,"Set up auto-transfer to savings on salary day. Spend what remains.","Salary day: auto-transfer to savings FIRST. Spend what's left.");
  add(2,"Saving","The 30-day rule for purchases means:",["Wait 30 days before non-essential purchases to see if you still want them","Buy within 30 minutes","Only shop once a month","Return items within 30 days"],0,"Most impulse buys seem unnecessary after 30 days. Saves significant money over time.","Want something? Wait 30 days. If you still want it then consider buying.");
  add(2,"Saving","Financial goals should be:",["Vague and flexible","Specific measurable achievable relevant and time-bound (SMART)","Only about retirement","Kept secret"],0,"Example: Save Rs 3 lakh for emergency fund in 18 months by saving Rs 17000 per month.","SMART goals: specific amount + timeline + plan = achievable savings.");
  add(2,"Saving","The latte factor concept teaches that:",["Small daily expenses compound into huge amounts over years","Coffee is unhealthy","Only large expenses matter","Cutting small expenses makes no difference"],0,"Rs 100 daily coffee = Rs 36500 per year. Invested at 12% for 20 years = Rs 26 lakh.","Rs 100/day = Rs 36500/year. Invested over 20 years = Rs 26 lakh. Small leaks sink ships.");
  add(2,"Banking","A fixed deposit gives higher interest than savings because:",["Your money is locked for a fixed period so the bank can plan its lending","Banks are generous","FDs have no risk","FDs are government guaranteed"],0,"Longer lock-in periods generally earn higher interest rates.","FD: higher interest but locked money. Choose tenure based on when you need funds.");
  add(2,"Banking","IMPS allows instant transfers:",["24x7 including holidays up to Rs 5 lakh","Only during banking hours","Only on weekdays","Once a week"],0,"IMPS works round the clock unlike NEFT which has batch processing. UPI also works 24x7.","IMPS and UPI: 24x7 instant transfers. NEFT: business hours batches.");
  add(2,"Banking","A joint account can be operated:",["Only by both holders together always","Either singly or jointly depending on the mandate chosen while opening","Only by the primary holder","Only by the bank"],0,"Choose 'either or survivor' for convenience or 'jointly' for safety.","Joint account: choose operating mode carefully. 'Either or Survivor' is most flexible.");
  add(2,"Banking","Minimum balance charges can be avoided by:",["Keeping less than minimum","Maintaining the required minimum balance or choosing zero-balance accounts like Jan Dhan","Ignoring bank notices","Closing the account"],0,"Several banks offer zero-balance savings accounts. PM Jan Dhan Yojana is one option.","Jan Dhan or zero-balance accounts avoid minimum balance penalties.");

  add(2,"Investment","Compound interest grows money exponentially because:",["Interest is earned on both the original amount AND previously accumulated interest","It pays higher rates","Banks add bonus amounts","Government subsidizes returns"],0,"Rs 1 lakh at 10% compound: year 1 = Rs 10K interest. Year 2 = Rs 11K. Year 10 = Rs 23.6K.","Compound interest: interest on interest. Start early — time is the multiplier.");
  add(2,"Investment","Rupee cost averaging means:",["Always buying at the lowest price","Investing fixed amounts regularly so you buy more units when cheap and fewer when expensive","Timing the market perfectly","Only investing when prices drop"],0,"Over time this smooths out market volatility and reduces average cost per unit.","SIP automates rupee cost averaging. No need to time the market.");
  add(2,"Investment","Asset allocation should be based on:",["Your age risk tolerance financial goals and time horizon","Only following what friends invest in","Always 100% in stocks","Only in FDs"],0,"Rule of thumb: 100 minus your age = equity percentage. Rest in debt. Adjust for risk tolerance.","Simple rule: equity% = 100 minus age. 30 years old = 70% equity 30% debt.");
  add(2,"Investment","PPF (Public Provident Fund) is attractive because:",["Government-backed safety with tax-free interest and Section 80C benefits","It has no lock-in","It gives 20% returns","It is only for government employees"],0,"15-year lock-in. EEE tax status (exempt at investment interest and withdrawal).","PPF: safe + tax-free + 80C benefit. 15-year lock-in. Start early.");
  add(2,"Investment","Gold as an investment is best for:",["Portfolio diversification and protection during economic uncertainty","Guaranteed high returns","Regular monthly income","Short-term profits"],0,"Gold doesn't generate income like stocks (dividends) or bonds (interest) but holds value during crises.","Gold: good for diversification. 5-10% of portfolio. Not for primary growth.");
  add(2,"Investment","Real estate as an investment is:",["Highly liquid and easy to sell","Relatively illiquid with high transaction costs but potential for long-term appreciation","Risk-free","Always profitable"],0,"Property involves stamp duty registration legal fees maintenance. Hard to sell quickly.","Real estate: long-term appreciation but illiquid. Don't put all savings in one property.");
  add(2,"Investment","A bear market means stocks have fallen:",["20% or more from recent highs signaling widespread pessimism","5% from recent highs","Any small amount","Exactly 10%"],0,"Bear markets are normal. They're the best time to buy for long-term investors through SIPs.","Bear market: 20%+ decline. Long-term investors: keep investing. Buy the dip via SIP.");
  add(2,"Investment","A bull market means stocks are:",["Rising 20%+ with widespread optimism and investor confidence","Falling sharply","Completely flat","Unpredictable"],0,"Bull markets can last years. Don't get overconfident — corrections are normal and healthy.","Bull market: rising prices optimism. Stay invested but don't over-leverage.");
  add(2,"Investment","Diversification reduces risk by:",["Spreading investments across different assets so poor performance in one is offset by others","Concentrating in one stock","Eliminating all risk","Only investing in gold"],0,"Don't put all eggs in one basket. Mix equity debt gold and international exposure.","Diversify: equity + debt + gold + international. No single point of failure.");
  add(2,"Investment","Market timing is:",["Easy and reliable","Extremely difficult — even professionals fail consistently. Time IN the market beats timing","Always successful with practice","Only for beginners"],0,"Missing the 10 best trading days over 20 years cuts returns by more than half.","Time IN the market > timing the market. Stay invested through SIPs.");

  add(2,"Insurance","The ideal health insurance sum insured for a family should be:",["At least Rs 5-10 lakh considering rising medical costs","Rs 1 lakh","Rs 50000","No health insurance needed"],0,"A single hospitalization can cost Rs 5-10 lakh. Medical inflation is 15% per year in India.","Health insurance: minimum Rs 5-10 lakh family cover. Medical costs are exploding.");
  add(2,"Insurance","Cashless hospitalization means:",["Insurance company pays the hospital directly so you don't pay from pocket at network hospitals","Hospital is completely free","You pay cash","Only government hospitals"],0,"Works only at network hospitals listed by your insurer. Carry your insurance card always.","Cashless = insurer pays hospital directly. Keep insurance card in wallet.");
  add(2,"Insurance","Life insurance is most needed by:",["People with financial dependents — spouse children or aging parents","Single people with no dependents","Only wealthy people","Only elderly people"],0,"If someone depends on your income buy term insurance worth 10-15x your annual income.","Have dependents? Buy term insurance = 10-15x annual income. Non-negotiable.");
  add(2,"Insurance","Insurance premium is:",["The amount you pay periodically for insurance coverage","The claim amount you receive","The policy number","The sum insured"],0,"Premiums vary based on age health coverage amount and policy type.","Premium = your periodic payment. Lower when you're young and healthy.");
  add(2,"Insurance","A deductible in health insurance means:",["The amount you must pay from pocket before insurance coverage starts","Free coverage amount","The premium","The maximum coverage"],0,"Higher deductible = lower premium. Choose based on your financial capacity.","Deductible = your share before insurance kicks in. Higher deductible = lower premium.");

  add(2,"Tax","TDS stands for:",["Tax Deducted at Source — automatically cut from income before you receive it","Total Deduction Summary","Transaction Debit Statement","Taxable Deduction Savings"],0,"Your employer or bank deducts TDS and deposits with government. File ITR to claim refunds.","TDS: tax auto-deducted from salary or interest. File ITR to get refund if excess deducted.");
  add(2,"Tax","Section 80D allows deduction for:",["Health insurance premiums up to Rs 25000 for self and Rs 50000 for senior citizen parents","Home loan interest","Education loans","Donations"],0,"Both individual and family health insurance premiums qualify under 80D.","80D: health insurance premium deduction. Rs 25K self + Rs 50K parents = Rs 75K total.");
  add(2,"Tax","Capital gains tax on equity held over 12 months:",["10% on gains above Rs 1 lakh per year without indexation","No tax at all","30% flat","Same as income tax"],0,"Short-term (under 12 months) equity gains are taxed at 15%.","LTCG on equity: 10% above Rs 1 lakh. STCG: 15%. Hold longer pay less.");
  add(2,"Tax","Filing ITR even when not mandatory is beneficial because:",["It creates a financial record useful for loans visa applications and claiming refunds","It is a waste of time","Only required for business owners","No benefit exists"],0,"Banks and visa officers check ITR history. Also necessary to claim TDS refunds.","Always file ITR: helps with loans visa and TDS refunds. Takes 15 minutes online.");
  add(2,"Tax","New tax regime vs old regime:",["New regime has lower rates but fewer deductions while old allows more deductions","They are identical","New regime always saves more","Old regime is abolished"],0,"Calculate both and choose the one that saves you more tax based on your investments.","Compare old vs new regime using tax calculator. Choose what saves YOU more.");

  add(2,"Fraud","Fake loan apps can be identified by:",["They ask access to contacts photos and gallery which is unnecessary for lending","They are all safe on app stores","They follow RBI guidelines","They charge standard rates"],0,"Real lenders don't need your gallery photos or contact list. Check RBI registration.","Loan app wants gallery and contacts? RED FLAG. Check RBI license before installing.");
  add(2,"Fraud","Cryptocurrency scams often promise:",["Guaranteed 100%+ monthly returns with zero risk","Normal market returns with risk disclosure","Low returns","No returns"],0,"No cryptocurrency or investment can guarantee fixed returns. All involve risk.","Guaranteed crypto returns = scam. 100% guaranteed. No exceptions.");
  add(2,"Fraud","The safest response to unknown money received in your account:",["Do not touch it — inform your bank immediately as it may be part of a fraud","Spend it immediately","Return it via UPI to the sender","Ignore it"],0,"Spending unknown deposits can make you part of a money laundering chain.","Unknown money in account: DO NOT touch. Inform bank immediately.");
  add(2,"Fraud","Advance fee fraud works by:",["Charging upfront fees for loans grants or prizes that never materialize","Legitimate processing fees","Standard business practice","Government tax collection"],0,"If you must pay to receive money it is always a scam. Legitimate winners never pay upfront.","Pay money to get money = SCAM. Always. Lottery job prize — all of them.");

  // ── LAW: 50 ──
  add(3,"Rights","Article 21 guarantees:",["Right to life and personal liberty","Right to equality","Right to education only","Right to property"],0,"The broadest fundamental right — courts have expanded it to include dignity privacy and livelihood.","Article 21: right to life + liberty. Courts expanded to include dignity and privacy.");
  add(3,"Rights","The Right to Education Act makes education:",["Free and compulsory for children aged 6-14 as a fundamental right","Optional for children","Free only in private schools","Compulsory until age 18"],0,"Schools must reserve 25% seats for economically weaker sections under RTE.","RTE: free compulsory education ages 6-14. 25% seats reserved for EWS.");
  add(3,"Rights","Right against exploitation prohibits:",["Forced labor trafficking and child labor under 14 in hazardous work","All types of employment","International trade","Government employment"],0,"Articles 23 and 24 protect against human trafficking forced labor and child exploitation.","No forced labor no child labor in hazardous work. Articles 23-24.");
  add(3,"Rights","A citizen can approach the Supreme Court directly for fundamental rights violation under:",["Article 32 — Right to Constitutional Remedies","Article 14","Article 19","Article 21 only"],0,"Dr. Ambedkar called Article 32 the heart and soul of the Constitution.","Article 32: direct access to Supreme Court for rights violations. Heart of Constitution.");
  add(3,"Constitution","The Preamble describes India as:",["A Sovereign Socialist Secular Democratic Republic","A Hindu nation","A constitutional monarchy","A purely federal state"],0,"These five words define India's constitutional identity and core values.","Sovereign Socialist Secular Democratic Republic. Know what each word means.");
  add(3,"Constitution","Amendments to the Constitution require:",["Simple majority","Special majority — 2/3rd of members present and voting in both houses","Unanimous vote","Public referendum"],0,"Some amendments also need ratification by half the state legislatures.","Constitutional amendment: 2/3rd majority in both houses. Very high bar.");
  add(3,"Constitution","Fundamental Rights are listed in:",["Part III of the Constitution","Part I","Part IV","Part V"],0,"6 Fundamental Rights: equality freedom against exploitation religion culture and constitutional remedies.","Part III: your 6 Fundamental Rights. Know them memorize them use them.");
  add(3,"Constitution","The Constitution was adopted on:",["November 26 1949 — now celebrated as Constitution Day","January 26 1950","August 15 1947","October 2 1950"],0,"It came into effect on January 26 1950 — Republic Day.","Adopted: Nov 26 1949 (Constitution Day). In effect: Jan 26 1950 (Republic Day).");
  add(3,"Constitution","India's Constitution draws from:",["Multiple sources — British US Irish Canadian Australian and other constitutions","Only British law","Only the US Constitution","Only ancient Indian texts"],0,"Fundamental rights from US directive principles from Ireland parliamentary system from Britain.","India's Constitution: best ideas from many democracies worldwide.");
  add(3,"Consumer","CCPA (Central Consumer Protection Authority) can:",["Impose penalties ban misleading ads and order product recalls","Only give warnings and order product recalls","Only write letters","Nothing — it has no power"],0,"CCPA was established under Consumer Protection Act 2019 with strong enforcement powers.","CCPA: real power to penalize misleading ads and protect consumers.");
  add(3,"Consumer","E-commerce companies must:",["Display total price provide return policies protect data and address grievances within 48 hours","Operate without rules","Only list products","Deliver in 1 hour always"],0,"Consumer Protection (E-Commerce) Rules 2020 regulate all online sellers and platforms.","Online sellers must show total price including all charges. Your right.");
  add(3,"Traffic","Hit and run cases can lead to:",["Up to 10 years imprisonment under IPC provisions","Only a fine","No legal consequence","Just license cancellation"],0,"Hit and run is a serious criminal offense. Always stop render help and report.","Hit and run: up to 10 years jail. STOP. Help the injured. Call 112.");
  add(3,"Traffic","Using mobile while driving attracts a fine of:",["Rs 1000-5000 depending on state","Rs 100","No fine exists","Rs 10"],0,"Distracted driving is a major killer. Even hands-free increases accident risk.","Phone while driving: Rs 1000-5000 fine. Not worth a life.");
  add(3,"Traffic","Driving without pollution certificate attracts:",["Rs 10000 fine for first offense under MV Act 2019","No penalty at all","Rs 50 fine","Warning only"],0,"PUC certificate ensures your vehicle meets emission standards. Get it tested every 6 months.","Get PUC certificate every 6 months. Rs 10000 fine without it.");
  add(3,"Governance","An ordinance is:",["A temporary law issued by the President when Parliament is not in session","A permanent law","A court order","A police directive"],0,"Ordinances must be approved by Parliament within 6 weeks of the next session or they expire.","Ordinance: temporary law when Parliament isn't sitting. Expires in 6 weeks.");
  add(3,"Governance","The Election Commission ensures:",["Free and fair elections in India","Budget allocation","Law enforcement","Tax collection"],0,"The ECI is an independent constitutional body that conducts elections at all levels.","Election Commission: independent body ensuring free fair elections.");
  add(3,"Governance","The CAG (Comptroller and Auditor General) is:",["An independent authority auditing all government expenditure and reporting to Parliament","A bank regulator","A tax collector","A military advisor"],0,"CAG ensures government money is spent properly. Called the guardian of the public purse.","CAG: audits government spending. Guardian of your tax money.");
  add(3,"Governance","Judicial review means:",["Courts can examine laws and government actions for constitutional validity","Judges reviewing each other","Parliament reviews courts","Executive reviews judiciary"],0,"If a law violates fundamental rights courts can strike it down as unconstitutional.","Judicial review: courts can strike down unconstitutional laws. Checks and balances.");
  add(3,"Women","The Domestic Violence Act protects:",["Women in any domestic relationship — wives live-in partners mothers sisters daughters","Only married women","Only women with children","Only women who file FIR first"],0,"Covers physical emotional sexual and economic abuse. Protection orders are available.","DV Act: protects women in all domestic relationships. Covers all types of abuse.");
  add(3,"Women","Sexual harassment at workplace — ICC is mandatory for:",["Only IT companies","Every organization with 10 or more employees","Only government offices","Only large corporations"],0,"Internal Complaints Committee must be constituted under the POSH Act 2013.","POSH Act: every workplace with 10+ employees must have an ICC. Zero tolerance.");

  // ── DIGITAL: 50 ──
  add(4,"Security","A password manager helps by:",["Generating and storing unique strong passwords for every account","Making all your passwords shorter","Sharing passwords with friends","Remembering only one weak password"],0,"You only remember one master password. The manager handles unique passwords for every site.","Use a password manager. One master password. Unique strong passwords everywhere.");
  add(4,"Security","Software updates should be installed:",["Promptly as they patch security vulnerabilities hackers already know about","Never — they slow your device","Only once a year","Only when forced"],0,"Delaying updates leaves known security holes open for attackers to exploit.","Update NOW not later. Hackers exploit known vulnerabilities within hours.");
  add(4,"Security","Juice jacking at public USB charging stations involves:",["Malware installation or data theft through modified USB ports","Only slow charging","No risk at all","Only affecting old phones"],0,"Use your own charger and wall outlet. Or carry a USB data blocker (charge-only cable).","Public USB ports can steal data. Use YOUR charger or a USB data blocker.");
  add(4,"Security","A phishing email can be identified by:",["Urgency pressure generic greetings suspicious links and requests for personal information","Perfect grammar always means phishing","Only by the email provider","Phishing is always obvious"],0,"Look for: urgency (act NOW) generic greeting (Dear Customer) suspicious sender address.","Phishing signs: urgency + generic greeting + suspicious link. When in doubt don't click.");
  add(4,"Security","End-to-end encryption protects:",["Only the sender","Messages so that only sender and recipient can read them — not even the app company","Messages from being sent","Only phone calls"],0,"WhatsApp Signal and some email services offer E2E encryption.","E2E encryption: only you and the recipient can read. Not even the app company.");
  add(4,"Privacy","Location sharing on social media should be:",["Carefully limited — real-time location reveals your exact whereabouts to strangers","Always on for all posts — real-time location reveals your exact whereabouts to strangers","Never a concern","Mandatory for all apps"],0,"Posting live location helps stalkers and burglars. Share location only with trusted contacts.","Turn OFF location in photos and posts. Share only with trusted contacts.");
  add(4,"Privacy","The 'right to be forgotten' means:",["Forgetting your own data","You can request removal of personal info from search engines and databases","Erasing the internet","Deleting others data"],0,"Useful for removing outdated information that harms your reputation or privacy.","Google allows personal info removal requests. Use it if needed.");
  add(4,"Privacy","Before clicking any link you should:",["Click immediately for speed","Check the URL by hovering verify the sender and question urgency","Never click any link ever","Only click links from friends"],0,"Even friend's accounts can be hacked and send malicious links. Verify before clicking.","Hover to check URL. Verify sender. Question urgency. When in doubt don't click.");
  add(4,"AI","ChatGPT and similar AI chatbots:",["Always provide perfectly accurate information","Can generate plausible-sounding responses that contain factual errors","Think and feel like humans","Are always wrong"],0,"AI is a powerful tool but not infallible. Cross-check important information independently.","AI is powerful but imperfect. Always verify critical information from reliable sources.");
  add(4,"AI","AI-generated content including text and images:",["Is always clearly marked","Can be virtually indistinguishable from human-created content making verification essential","Is always low quality","Only affects social media"],0,"As AI content becomes more realistic critical evaluation of sources becomes more important.","AI content can look completely real. Develop critical evaluation skills.");
  add(4,"Digital Life","Digital wellbeing means:",["Having the fastest internet","Maintaining a healthy relationship with technology balancing screen time with real life","Owning the latest gadgets","Having many social media followers"],0,"Set screen time limits take digital breaks and prioritize in-person connections.","Digital wellbeing: set limits take breaks prioritize real connections.");
  add(4,"Digital Life","Children's online safety requires:",["No supervision at all","Active parental involvement age-appropriate content settings and open conversations","Only blocking everything","Giving children unlimited access"],0,"Balance protection with education. Teach children to recognize online dangers.","Talk to children about online safety. Monitor don't just block.");
  add(4,"Fake News","Fact-checking websites in India include:",["Only Wikipedia","Alt News Boom FactChecker and India Today Fact Check","Only social media comments","No fact-checkers exist in India"],0,"Before sharing sensational news check these sites. Also verify using official sources.","Before sharing: check Alt News or Boom. If only one source claims it be skeptical.");
  add(4,"Fake News","Misinformation spreads faster on social media because:",["Social media companies promote it","Emotional and sensational content gets more engagement and shares than boring truth","Only fake news is interesting","People verify everything they share"],0,"Pause before sharing. Ask: is this verified? Is the source credible? Am I being manipulated?","STOP before sharing. Is it verified? Is the source credible? If not don't forward.");
  add(4,"Internet","Cookie consent popups on websites ask permission to:",["Track your browsing behavior and store preferences through small data files","Hack your computer","Delete your history","Access your camera"],0,"Cookies can be useful for preferences but tracking cookies follow you across websites.","Review cookie settings. Accept necessary only. Reject tracking cookies when possible.");
  add(4,"Internet","A VPN is most important when:",["Using public WiFi networks at cafes airports and hotels","At home on your private WiFi","Browsing social media at home","Reading news websites"],0,"VPN encrypts your traffic making it unreadable even if intercepted on public networks.","Public WiFi = VPN mandatory. Your data is exposed without it.");

  // ── CRITICAL THINKING: 50 ──
  add(9,"Logic","Cherry-picking data means:",["Choosing only evidence supporting your argument while ignoring contradicting evidence","Selecting the best quality data","Organizing data","Collecting all available data"],0,"Advertisers politicians and media cherry-pick statistics to support their narrative.","Watch for cherry-picked stats. Ask: what data are they NOT showing?");
  add(9,"Logic","The Texas sharpshooter fallacy involves:",["Drawing conclusions first then finding data to support them while ignoring the rest","Expert marksmanship","Texas politics","Statistical accuracy"],0,"Like shooting at a barn then painting the target around the bullet holes.","Conclusion first evidence second = Texas sharpshooter. Real science works opposite.");
  add(9,"Logic","Selection bias means:",["The sample studied is not representative of the full population leading to skewed results","Selecting the best candidates","Random sampling","Equal representation"],0,"Online polls are biased because they only capture opinions of people who choose to respond.","Beware selection bias. Ask: does this sample represent the whole population?");
  add(9,"Logic","The Gambler's Fallacy is believing:",["Past random events influence future random events like a coin being due for heads","Gambling always loses money","Skill determines all outcomes","All gambling is fair"],0,"Each coin flip is independent. 10 heads in a row doesn't make tails more likely on flip 11.","Each coin flip is independent. Past doesn't influence future random events.");
  add(9,"Logic","A red herring in arguments is:",["An irrelevant topic introduced to distract from the real issue being discussed","A strong counterpoint","A valid concern","Supporting evidence"],0,"Politicians often use red herrings to avoid answering difficult questions.","Red herring: irrelevant distraction from the real issue. Stay focused on the topic.");
  add(9,"Logic","Whataboutism deflects criticism by:",["Pointing to someone else's wrongdoing instead of addressing the actual criticism","Addressing the issue directly","Providing evidence","Accepting responsibility"],0,"Responding to climate change criticism with 'but China pollutes more' doesn't address the issue.","Whataboutism: deflects instead of addressing. Both things can be wrong simultaneously.");
  add(9,"Logic","Post hoc fallacy means assuming:",["Because event B happened after event A then A caused B","Proper logical order","Events are unrelated","Time doesn't matter"],0,"I wore lucky socks and we won doesn't mean the socks caused the victory.","After ≠ because of. Sequence doesn't prove causation.");
  add(9,"Logic","The burden of proof falls on:",["The person making a claim to provide evidence","The person questioning the claim","Nobody","The audience"],0,"If someone claims a miracle cure THEY must prove it. You don't have to disprove it.","Extraordinary claims need extraordinary evidence. Burden is on the claimer.");
  add(9,"Bias","Availability heuristic makes people:",["Overestimate the likelihood of events that are easily recalled like plane crashes","Remember everything accurately","Forget everything","Always think rationally"],0,"We fear plane crashes more than car accidents despite cars being far more dangerous.","We overestimate vivid memorable risks and underestimate common boring ones.");
  add(9,"Bias","The endowment effect means:",["People value things they own more than identical things they don't own","Giving things away easily","Buying more things","Ignoring possessions"],0,"This is why we overvalue our old phone but wouldn't pay the same for someone else's identical one.","You overvalue what you own. Be objective when deciding to keep or sell.");
  add(9,"Bias","Status quo bias is the preference for:",["The current state of affairs even when better alternatives exist","Change and innovation","High social status","New experiences"],0,"People stick with their bank phone plan and habits even when switching would save money.","We prefer familiar even when change is better. Periodically audit your choices.");
  add(9,"Bias","The Barnum effect explains why people believe:",["Vague personality descriptions like horoscopes that seem accurate but apply to almost everyone","Scientific studies","Weather forecasts","Expert opinions"],0,"Horoscopes work because statements like 'you sometimes feel insecure' apply to everyone.","Horoscopes seem accurate because they're vague enough to fit anyone. That's the Barnum effect.");
  add(9,"Bias","Negativity bias means humans:",["Give more weight to negative experiences than equally positive ones","Are always negative people","Ignore all negative info","Only remember good things"],0,"One criticism stings more than ten compliments. Evolution wired us to focus on threats.","One insult hurts more than ten compliments help. That's negativity bias. Counter it consciously.");
  add(9,"Bias","Ingroup bias makes people:",["Favor their own group while being less favorable to outsiders","Treat everyone equally","Hate their own group","Have no preferences"],0,"This drives tribalism from sports teams to politics to nationalism.","We naturally favor our group. Recognize this bias and judge people as individuals.");
  add(9,"Decision","The regret minimization framework suggests:",["At age 80 which choice would you regret NOT making? Choose that","Avoiding all decisions","Only considering short-term effects","Following others always"],0,"Jeff Bezos used this framework when deciding to leave his job and start Amazon.","Big decision? Ask your 80-year-old self: which choice would I regret NOT making?");
  add(9,"Decision","Mental models are:",["Thinking frameworks that help you understand how the world works and make better decisions","3D brain scans","Only for scientists","Computer simulations"],0,"Examples: first principles inversion Pareto 80/20 second-order thinking.","Build a toolkit of mental models: 80/20 inversion first principles second-order thinking.");
  add(9,"Ethics","Whistleblowing is important because it:",["Exposes wrongdoing that might otherwise harm the public or remain hidden","Creates unnecessary problems","Is always rewarded","Only affects competitors"],0,"India's Whistle Blowers Protection Act protects those who expose corruption.","Whistleblowers expose corruption and save lives. They deserve protection.");
  add(9,"Ethics","Corporate social responsibility means:",["Companies voluntarily acting in ways that benefit society beyond legal requirements","Only maximizing shareholder profit","Marketing strategy only","Tax avoidance technique"],0,"Indian companies above Rs 5 crore net profit must spend 2% on CSR under Companies Act.","CSR: Indian law requires eligible companies to spend 2% profit on social good.");
  add(9,"Ethics","Ethical decision-making requires considering:",["Impact on all stakeholders long-term consequences fairness and principles","Only your personal benefit","Only legal requirements","Only profit margins"],0,"The newspaper test: would you be comfortable if your decision was on tomorrow's front page?","Ethical test: would you be comfortable if this decision made front-page news?");
  add(9,"Mental Models","Inversion thinking means:",["Instead of asking how to succeed ask what would guarantee failure then avoid those things","Thinking backwards is wrong","Inverting all decisions","Being contrarian"],0,"Want a great marriage? List everything that destroys marriages and avoid all of those.","Inversion: instead of 'how to succeed' ask 'what guarantees failure' and avoid it.");

  // ── MIXED AWARENESS: 90 ──
  add(11,"Sports","How many players in a cricket team on the field?",["11","9","13","15"],0,"Cricket teams have 11 players including the captain wicketkeeper bowlers and fielders.","Cricket: 11 players per team.");
  add(11,"Sports","A century in cricket means the batsman scored:",["100 runs in an innings","50 runs","200 runs","150 runs"],0,"Scoring 100 is a landmark achievement. A double century is 200 runs.","Century = 100 runs. Half-century = 50. Double century = 200.");
  add(11,"Sports","In cricket an over consists of:",["6 balls","4 balls","8 balls","5 balls"],0,"A bowler bowls 6 legal deliveries per over. Wides and no-balls are extras.","One over = 6 balls. Wide or no-ball = extra ball.");
  add(11,"Sports","The FIFA World Cup is held every:",["4 years","2 years","Every year","3 years"],0,"The tournament features 32 (now 48 from 2026) national teams competing over a month.","FIFA World Cup: every 4 years. 48 teams from 2026.");
  add(11,"Sports","How many players in a football (soccer) team on the field?",["11","9","13","7"],0,"11 per side including goalkeeper. Standard match is 90 minutes (two 45-minute halves).","Football: 11 players per side. 90 minutes match.");
  add(11,"Sports","The Olympics are held every:",["4 years with summer and winter alternating every 2 years","2 years","Every year","5 years"],0,"Summer Olympics every 4 years. Winter Olympics also every 4 years offset by 2 years.","Olympics: every 4 years. Summer and Winter alternate every 2 years.");
  add(11,"Sports","Chess originated in:",["Ancient India where it was called Chaturanga","Russia","China","Greece"],0,"Chaturanga evolved through Persia and Arabia into modern chess. India's gift to world gaming.","Chess originated in ancient India as Chaturanga. Spread worldwide.");
  add(11,"Sports","Kabaddi originated in:",["India","China","Japan","Korea"],0,"Kabaddi is one of India's indigenous sports. Pro Kabaddi League made it hugely popular.","Kabaddi: ancient Indian sport. Now a professional league sensation.");
  add(11,"Sports","A marathon covers approximately:",["42.195 km (26.2 miles)","21 km","50 km","10 km"],0,"Named after the Battle of Marathon. A half marathon is 21.1 km.","Marathon = 42.195 km. Half marathon = 21.1 km. Train properly before attempting.");
  add(11,"Sports","How many players in a basketball team on the court?",["5 per side","7 per side","6 per side","11 per side"],0,"5 players per team on court. Matches have 4 quarters of 10-12 minutes each.","Basketball: 5 per side on court.");
  add(11,"Sports","The sport of badminton originated in:",["British India","China","USA","Japan"],0,"Named after Badminton House in England where British officers played a version they learned in India.","Badminton: originated in India refined in England. India has strong Olympic heritage in it.");
  add(11,"Sports","In tennis a score of zero is called:",["Love","Null","Blank","Zero"],0,"The origin is debated — possibly from French 'l'oeuf' meaning egg shaped like zero.","Tennis scoring: love (0) 15 30 40 game. Deuce at 40-40.");
  add(11,"Sports","The Tour de France is a famous:",["Cycling race — the most prestigious in the world","Running marathon","Car race","Swimming competition"],0,"Approximately 3500 km over 23 days through the French countryside and mountains.","Tour de France: world's biggest cycling race. ~3500 km over 23 days.");
  add(11,"Sports","The Ashes is a cricket series between:",["England and Australia","India and Pakistan","India and England","South Africa and England"],0,"Named after a satirical obituary in 1882 saying English cricket had died and its ashes taken to Australia.","The Ashes: England vs Australia. One of cricket's oldest rivalries.");
  add(11,"Sports","Polo is played on:",["Horseback","Foot","Bicycles","Ice"],0,"One of the oldest team sports. Manipur India claims to be the birthplace of modern polo.","Polo: played on horseback. India (Manipur) claims its origin.");

  add(11,"Awareness","The most widely spoken language by native speakers globally is:",["Mandarin Chinese","English","Spanish","Hindi"],0,"About 920 million native Mandarin speakers. English has the most total speakers including non-native.","Mandarin: most native speakers. English: most total speakers worldwide.");
  add(11,"Awareness","Diamond is a form of:",["Carbon — same element as graphite and coal","Gold","Silver","Platinum"],0,"Diamond and graphite are both pure carbon arranged in different crystal structures.","Diamond = carbon. Same element as pencil graphite but different arrangement.");
  add(11,"Awareness","How many colors are in a rainbow?",["7 — violet indigo blue green yellow orange red (VIBGYOR)","5","6","8"],0,"White light splits into 7 colors when refracted through water droplets.","Rainbow VIBGYOR: Violet Indigo Blue Green Yellow Orange Red.");
  add(11,"Awareness","Earth takes approximately how long to orbit the Sun?",["365.25 days — which is why we have leap years every 4 years","24 hours","30 days","7 days"],0,"The extra 0.25 days accumulate to 1 extra day every 4 years giving us February 29.","Earth orbit: 365.25 days. The 0.25 gives us leap years.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The Statue of Unity depicts:",["Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel — the Iron Man of India","Mahatma Gandhi","Jawaharlal Nehru","Dr. B.R. Ambedkar"],0,"At 182 meters it is the tallest statue in the world located in Gujarat.","Statue of Unity: 182m. Tallest in the world. Sardar Patel. Gujarat.");
  add(11,"Awareness","India is the world's largest producer of:",["Milk — thanks to Operation Flood and the cooperative movement","Wheat","Rice","Corn"],0,"India produces over 200 million tonnes of milk annually. Verghese Kurien led the revolution.","India: world's largest milk producer. Operation Flood transformed dairy.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The binary number system uses only:",["0 and 1 — the foundation of all digital computing","Numbers 0-9","Letters A-F","Numbers 1-10"],0,"Every file photo video and program on your computer is stored as combinations of 0s and 1s.","Binary: 0 and 1. Every digital thing you use runs on this. Fundamental.");
  add(11,"Awareness","Fingerprints are:",["Unique to every individual — no two people have ever had the same prints","Identical in identical twins","Same within families","They change with age"],0,"Even identical twins have different fingerprints. Formed in the womb by random factors.","Fingerprints: unique to YOU. Even identical twins differ. Used since 1892 for identification.");
  add(11,"Awareness","Honey never spoils because:",["Its low moisture content and acidic pH create conditions where bacteria cannot survive","It contains preservatives","It is artificial","It is frozen"],0,"Edible honey has been found in Egyptian tombs over 3000 years old.","Honey: 3000-year-old honey from Egyptian tombs was still edible.");
  add(11,"Awareness","Octopuses have:",["3 hearts — two pump blood to gills and one to the rest of the body","1 heart","2 hearts","4 hearts"],0,"They also have blue blood (copper-based) and 9 brains (1 central plus 1 in each arm).","Octopus: 3 hearts 9 brains blue blood. Nature's alien.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The fastest land animal is:",["Cheetah reaching up to 112 km/h in short bursts","Lion","Horse","Tiger"],0,"Cheetahs can accelerate from 0 to 100 km/h in 3 seconds but tire quickly.","Cheetah: 0-100 km/h in 3 seconds. Faster than most sports cars.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The largest animal ever to live on Earth is:",["Blue whale — up to 30 meters long and 170 tonnes","Any dinosaur","African elephant","Great white shark"],0,"Blue whale hearts are the size of a small car. Their tongue alone weighs as much as an elephant.","Blue whale: largest animal EVER. Bigger than any dinosaur.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The Wright Brothers made the first powered flight in:",["1903 — the flight lasted 12 seconds covering 37 meters","1890","1910","1920"],0,"Their first flight at Kitty Hawk North Carolina lasted just 12 seconds.","First flight: 1903. 12 seconds. 37 meters. Changed the world forever.");
  add(11,"Awareness","Paper was invented in:",["Ancient China around 105 AD by Cai Lun","Egypt","India","Greece"],0,"Before paper people wrote on bamboo silk papyrus and animal skin.","Paper: Chinese invention ~105 AD. Revolutionized knowledge sharing.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The Nobel Prize for Peace is awarded in:",["Oslo Norway — while all other Nobels are in Stockholm","Stockholm Sweden","Geneva Switzerland","New York USA"],0,"Nobel specified Peace Prize be awarded by a Norwegian committee. His personal wish.","Peace Prize: Oslo. All other Nobels: Stockholm. Alfred Nobel's specific wish.");
  add(11,"Awareness","Zero was developed as a mathematical concept by:",["Indian mathematicians — Aryabhata and Brahmagupta made key contributions","Greek mathematicians","Roman mathematicians","Egyptian mathematicians"],0,"Brahmagupta (628 CE) first defined rules for arithmetic with zero.","Zero: India's greatest gift to mathematics. Brahmagupta 628 CE.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The approximate age of Earth is:",["About 4.5 billion years","1 million years","100 million years","10000 years"],0,"Determined through radiometric dating of rocks and meteorites.","Earth: 4.5 billion years old. Humans appeared only ~300000 years ago.");
  add(11,"Awareness","Wi-Fi is:",["Actually just a brand name that does not stand for anything","An abbreviation for Wireless Fidelity","Short for Wide Field Internet","An abbreviation for Wireless Finder"],0,"The Wi-Fi Alliance chose the name because it sounded catchy. It has no official full form.","Wi-Fi: just a brand name. No official full form.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The most recycled material in the world is:",["Steel (iron) — it can be recycled infinitely without losing quality","Plastic","Paper","Glass"],0,"Steel is 100% recyclable and the most recycled material by weight globally.","Steel: most recycled material. 100% recyclable. Infinitely reusable.");
  add(11,"Awareness","Sharks have existed on Earth longer than:",["Trees — sharks appeared about 450 million years ago while trees appeared 350 million years ago","Humans only","Fish","Insects"],0,"Sharks predate trees by 100 million years and dinosaurs by 200 million years.","Sharks: older than trees and dinosaurs. 450 million years of evolution.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The human nose can detect approximately:",["About 1 trillion different scents","1000 scents","10000 scents","100 scents"],0,"Research from Rockefeller University in 2014 showed the nose can distinguish a trillion smells.","Your nose: 1 trillion scents. Far more sophisticated than previously thought.");
  add(11,"Awareness","A group of lions is called a:",["Pride","Herd","Pack","Flock"],0,"A pride typically consists of related females their cubs and a small number of adult males.","Pride of lions. Pack of wolves. School of fish. Flock of birds.");
  add(11,"Awareness","A group of wolves is called a:",["Pack","Herd","Pride","School"],0,"Wolf packs have a complex social hierarchy with alpha pair leading.","Pack of wolves. They hunt cooperatively and have strong family bonds.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The tallest animal is the:",["Giraffe — adults can reach 5.5 meters (18 feet) tall","Elephant","Ostrich","Horse"],0,"Despite their long necks giraffes have the same number of neck vertebrae as humans — seven.","Giraffe: tallest at 5.5m. Same 7 neck vertebrae as humans. Each one is much longer.");
  add(11,"Awareness","Bamboo is technically classified as:",["A type of grass — the largest in the grass family","A tree","A shrub","A fern"],0,"Some bamboo species can grow 91 cm (36 inches) in a single day — the fastest growing plant.","Bamboo: a grass not a tree. Can grow 91 cm in ONE DAY.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The Great Pacific Garbage Patch is:",["A massive accumulation of floating plastic debris in the Pacific Ocean","A landfill on an island","A recycling center","A natural rock formation"],0,"Estimated at 1.6 million square km — twice the size of Texas. Mostly microplastics.","Pacific Garbage Patch: 2x Texas size. Mostly microplastics. Reduce plastic use.");
  add(11,"Awareness","How many bones does a newborn baby have?",["206 like adults","About 270 — many fuse together as the child grows","150","300"],0,"Adults have 206 bones. Babies have more because many bones haven't fused yet.","Baby: ~270 bones. Adult: 206. Bones fuse together as you grow.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The Mona Lisa was painted by:",["Leonardo da Vinci in the early 1500s","Michelangelo","Raphael","Rembrandt"],0,"It hangs in the Louvre museum in Paris and is the most visited artwork in the world.","Mona Lisa: Leonardo da Vinci. Early 1500s. Louvre Paris.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The first human to walk on the Moon was:",["Neil Armstrong on July 20 1969 during the Apollo 11 mission","Buzz Aldrin","Yuri Gagarin","John Glenn"],0,"Armstrong's words: 'That's one small step for man one giant leap for mankind.'","Neil Armstrong: first on the Moon. July 20 1969. Apollo 11.");
  add(11,"Awareness","How many teeth does a normal adult have?",["28","32 including 4 wisdom teeth","30","36"],0,"28 without wisdom teeth 32 with them. Wisdom teeth often need extraction.","Adult teeth: 32 (including 4 wisdom teeth).");
  add(11,"Awareness","The hardest natural substance on Earth is:",["Diamond","Steel","Gold","Platinum"],0,"Diamond scores 10 on the Mohs hardness scale. It can only be scratched by another diamond.","Diamond: hardest natural substance. Score 10 on Mohs scale.");
  add(11,"Awareness","The human body contains approximately how many liters of blood?",["About 5 liters for an average adult","2-3 liters","8-10 liters","1 liter"],0,"5 liters circulated by the heart which beats about 100000 times per day.","5 liters of blood. Heart pumps it 100000 times daily. Impressive engine.");
  add(11,"Awareness","India's national anthem Jana Gana Mana was written by:",["Rabindranath Tagore","Bankim Chandra Chattopadhyay","Mahatma Gandhi","Jawaharlal Nehru"],0,"First sung at the Calcutta session of Indian National Congress on December 27 1911.","National anthem: Tagore. National song (Vande Mataram): Bankim Chandra.");
